output.final_deliverable:
1) What Docker is (brief): Docker helps you containerize applications — the official Docker documentation describes itself as the library of resources, manuals, and guides to help you containerize applications (source: https://docs.docker.com/).

2) Latest stable version number: The documentation lists the current Engine release series as "Engine v29" (source: https://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/). A more specific patch/version string (for example v29.x.y) was not visible in the retrieved content, so I cannot state a more precise patch version from the visited pages.

3) Three key features / capabilities (from the official docs):
- Containerization (build and run containers / images) — docs emphasize helping you containerize applications (source: https://docs.docker.com/).
- Docker Compose for defining and running multi-container applications (section shown in the Engine docs) (source: https://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/ and the Compose documentation links on the docs site).
- Engine capabilities for storage and networking: volumes, bind mounts, and multiple network drivers / port publishing (these topics are listed in the Engine documentation) (source: https://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/).

4) Installation guide link: Official installation instructions are at https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/ (source: https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/ as referenced from the docs).
output.action_summary: I visited the official Docker documentation homepage (https://docs.docker.com/) and the Docker Engine release notes / manual index (https://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/). From those pages I extracted a brief definition (that Docker helps you containerize applications), the documented current Engine release series (Engine v29), three documented features (containerization, Docker Compose, storage & networking capabilities), and the installation guide link (https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/). A specific patch-level version number was not visible in the retrieved page content, so I reported the release series (v29) and noted the lack of a more precise version in the visited content.
